,Recommended,403700,19183572,"Posted: 20 November, 2015",all,maplesyrupghost,"This is such a great game.  Yahtzee's YouTube series ""Zero Punctuation"" has always been super entertaining but now he has brought us an equally-random experience that is now only interactive but endlessly unique every time around.  If you are a fan of his show, you will enjoy this game, definitely!You get gifts for collecting enough hats, and most of the hats offer a unique twist on the gameplay.  Some were more pointless than others but the whole game experience is affected in at least some way by each present.The gameplay is quite simple.  There is a hat falling and you have to stand under it.  With each hat you get, it gets harder and harder, with multiple objects falling at once (and you have to guess which is the hat and which is something less enjoyable like an anvil) and you advance if you guess correctly.  It can get very difficult when there are clones of yourself and you have to figure out which person you are controlling -- all in a matter of a few seconds.  If you are really bad, you will still gain presents as it retains however many points achieved.  High score is also tracked, but I love it how you will still get hats towards the ultimate prize even if you can only last through the first few stages.  I'm not entirely sure what the gift is if you get 1500 hats.  I guess I'll have to keep playing to find out!Overall, a great game, worth a buy.  It's not much more than that -- a minigames and funny commentary -- so if you are expecting something more than that maybe wait for a sale.  But for Zero Punctuation fans, it's a buy."
