,Recommended,403700,19261873,"Posted: 24 November, 2015",all,RvB Caboose,It has hats
,Recommended,403700,19180502,"Posted: 20 November, 2015",all,DD [The Dignitary],"Hatfall is a great game. Combining both challenging and fun gameplay, Hatfall is sure to leave you on your toes.To explain on this a bit, let's talk about the gameplay. You play as Yahtzee (famous from Zero Punctuation) who has lost his hat. Whilst this may not sound like something interesting, believe me it's quite fun. It combines a mechanic found often in mobile games, namely short and quick reaction gameplay. Your task is to get Yahtzee his nice looking hat back. Every 25 hats you get to choose between ""gifts"" indicated by the progress bar on the sections below the level. Said gifts, when unlocked, frequently permit a minigame to be unlocked: e.g. Unlocking Hatsassin's Creed causes you to be dropped of in a clear parody of a dating sim.The game itself doesn't prefer to play nice on you. Instead it favors to downright insult the player. In-between level sections and a second before the level begins, you get a pop-up message. These message always involve doing something with a hat. If you succeed, you are greeted with another popup message, which always involves boosting Yahtzee's massive ego or make more fun about hats. But those things are insulting to the player who doesn't know what Zero Punctuation is: A webshow about reviewing Video Games on their negative points. Of course the game was going to be insulting.Although I don't know what the 1500 hat collective does yet, it will probably involve Yahtzee laughing at me for wasting my time on this great addictive game."
